Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new algorithm for self-supervised reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the use of self-supervised goal setting to enable an agent to propose its own goals and acquire skills, which is a common topic in the field of AI. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper presents experiments with a real robot to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method in learning manipulation tasks, which falls under the category of robotics. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper uses images as input to learn manipulation tasks, which is a common application of computer vision in robotics. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a formal exploration objective for goal-reaching policies, which is related to the field of systems and control.
